a, and the Asian and Latin American labor flows powering global capitalism today. Read together, Asian American and Latinx literatures convey astonishing diversity and untapped possibilities for coalition within the United States' fastest-growing immigrant and minority communities; to understand the changing shape of these communities we must see how they have formed in relation to each other. As the U.S. population approaches a minority-majority threshold, we urgently need methods that can look across the divisions and unequal positions of the racial system. Giving Form to an Asian and Latinx America leads the way with a vision for the future built on panethnic and cross-racial solidarity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAmerican fictionxAsian American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican fictionxHispanic American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican fictionxMinority authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAsian Americans in literature. 0aHispanic Americans in literature. 0aImmigrants in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican literature.  aAsian American.  aCold War.  aLatinx.  acomparative racialization.  aimmigration.  aneoliberalism.  apanethnicity.  apost-civil rights.  atransfictional form.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uh